#. lang="pi"><section class="sutta" id="thag2.34"><article><div
#. class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "thag2.34:1.1"
msgid "Theragāthā"
msgstr "Verses of the Senior Monks"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "thag2.34:2.1"
msgid "Dukanipāta"
msgstr "The Book of the Twos"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "thag2.34:3.1"
msgid "Catutthavagga"
msgstr "Chapter Four"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "thag2.34:4.1"
msgid "2.34. Isidinnattheragāthā"
msgstr "2.34. Isidinna"

#. </h1></div><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a
#. class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc187"></a><a class="verse-num-pts"
#. id="verse-num-pts187"></a>
msgctxt "thag2.34:5.1"
msgid "“Diṭṭhā mayā dhammadharā upāsakā,"
msgstr "I’ve seen lay disciples who have memorized discourses,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag2.34:5.2"
msgid "Kāmā aniccā iti bhāsamānā;"
msgstr "saying, “Sensual pleasures are impermanent”."

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag2.34:5.3"
msgid "Sārattarattā maṇikuṇḍalesu,"
msgstr "But they’re infatuated with jewels and earrings,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag2.34:5.4"
msgid "Puttesu dāresu ca te apekkhā."
msgstr "concerned for their partners and children."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc188"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts188"></a>
msgctxt "thag2.34:6.1"
msgid "Addhā na jānanti yatodha dhammaṃ,"
msgstr "To be honest, they don’t know Dhamma,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag2.34:6.2"
msgid "Kāmā aniccā iti cāpi āhu;"
msgstr "even though they say “Sensual pleasures are impermanent”."

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag2.34:6.3"
msgid "Rāgañca tesaṃ na balatthi chettuṃ,"
msgstr "They don’t have the power to cut their lust,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag2.34:6.4"
msgid "Tasmā sitā puttadāraṃ dhanañcā”ti."
msgstr "which is why they cling to children, wives, and wealth."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "thag2.34:7.1"
msgid "…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "thag2.34:7.2"
msgid "Isidinno thero …."
msgstr ""
